<p>This is my prolog file.</p>  <pre><code>male(bob). male(john).  female(betty). female(dana).  father(bob, john). father(bob, dana). mother(betty, john). mother(betty, dana).  daughter(X, Y) :- female(X), mother(Y, X). </code></pre>  <p>I want to query something like this <code>daughter(X, mother(Y, john)).</code> Is it possible?</p>  <p>I'm trying to get daughter of john's mother.</p>  <p>I got this idea from <a href="http://www.cse.unsw.edu.au/~billw/cs9414/notes/prolog/intro.html" rel="nofollow">here</a> under 'Asking Questions with Structures'</p>